# TypeScript Code Style

- **Naming**: Avoid short names; prefer descriptive identifiers. Functions are verbs; variables are nouns
- **Types**: Explicitly annotate function signatures and public APIs; avoid `any`
- **Control Flow**: Prefer early returns; handle errors and edge cases first
- **Comments**: Only where helpful, explaining "why" not "how"; no TODOs
- **Formatting**: Match existing formatting; avoid large unrelated reformatting
- **React**: Use function components and hooks; keep props typed; avoid unnecessary re-renders
- **Imports**: Group by standard, third-party, internal; avoid deep relative paths when aliases exist
